## Accessibility Checklist

### Must-Have (WCAG 2.1 Level AA)

- [ ] All images have alt text
- [ ] All form inputs have labels
- [ ] All buttons have accessible names
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works everywhere
- [ ] Focus indicators are visible (3px outline)
- [ ] Color contrast is 4.5:1 minimum
- [ ] Headings are properly nested (h1 ‚Üí h2 ‚Üí h3)
- [ ] ARIA labels on custom components
- [ ] Skip links for keyboard users
- [ ] Status messages use aria-live

### Should-Have (WCAG 2.1 Level AAA)

- [ ] Color contrast is 7:1 (enhanced)
- [ ] Text can resize to 200% without breakage
- [ ] Touch targets are 44x44px minimum
- [ ] Animations respect prefers-reduced-motion
- [ ] Help text available for complex interactions
- [ ] Error messages are descriptive, not just "Invalid"

### Testing Checklist

- [ ] Navigate entire app with keyboard only (no mouse)
- [ ] Use screen reader (VoiceOver/NVDA/JAWS)
- [ ] Test at 200% browser zoom
- [ ] Test with high contrast mode
- [ ] Test with CSS disabled (semantic HTML still works)
- [ ] Test with JavaScript disabled (core functionality works)

