## Feature 4: Local Bulletin Boards

### Concept

**What it is:** Digital bulletin boards tied to physical locations. Only visible when nearby.

**Example:**
```
üìå Writers' Circle: Bluestone Caf√© Board

[You're at Bluestone Caf√© - 4 new posts]

‚Ä¢ Maya (2h ago): "Anyone want to workshop a short story?"
‚Ä¢ Alex (yesterday): "Writing here Tuesday 3pm, join?"
‚Ä¢ Jordan (3 days ago): "Left a book on table 7, yours if you want"
‚Ä¢ Sam (1 week ago): "Open mic night ideas?"

[Post to board] [View archive]
```

---

### Why This Matters

**Creates micro-communities:**
- Encourages face-to-face meetups
- Tied to real places people already go
- Ephemeral (posts expire after 30 days)
- Local only (not global feed)

**Use cases:**
- Study groups meeting at libraries
- Writers meeting at caf√©s
- Artists at galleries
- Classes at specific buildings
- Community at parks

